Ghana’s Gold Production Rose 1.4% in 2010, Revenue Up 27.5%

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-03-08T12:19:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/ghana-s-gold-production-rose-1-4-in-2010-revenue-up-27-5-2-.html
Gold production in  Ghana ,  Africa ’s
largest producer of the metal after  South Africa , rose 1.4
percent to 2.97 million ounces in 2010 from a year earlier,
according to data from the  Ghana  Chamber of Mines.  Revenue from sales of the precious metal during the year
increased 27.5 percent to $3.62 billion, the Accra-based group
said in an e-mailed statement today.  Gold is Ghana’s biggest export earner, accounting for 48
percent of the revenue the country made from exports in 2010,
the  Bank of Ghana  said Feb. 18.  Diamond production declined 13 percent to 308,679 carats,
while revenue from sales of the gems rose 59.2 percent to $11.13
million, the Chamber of Mines said.  Bauxite output during the year expanded 4.5 percent to
512,208 metric tons, while earnings from sales of the raw
material used to make aluminum increased 35.8 percent to $15.15
million, it said.  The West African nation’s manganese production rose 17.8
percent to 1.19 million tons, while earnings from the metal
increased 20 percent to $77.81 million, the chamber said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  